review_blob: I was recently reminded how crummy these corn-fed american beers really are.  I was on a long range fishing boat at the beginning of June and forgot to bring some real beer with me.  My choices were Bud, Coors Light, and Miller GD.  Well, I chose GD - once.  From that point on it was Rum and Coke!
A great beer - right in my backyard.  If you havent had this one on tap I highly recommend it.
A very good American Pale Ale.
When I first had this one back in college I wasnt ready for it.  Over time bocks have become some of my favorite brews and Celebrator is at the top of the list.

One of my favorite fruit beers.  Heavy apricot aroma while the fruit taste isnt too overwhelming.  As fruit beers go they are either way too fruity or you cant taste the fruit at all.  Pyramids Apricot is right down the center.
A good alternative to Harpoons Winter Warmer since Harpoon is not yet distributed on the West Coast.
beer_name: Buffalo Bills Americas Original Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: At first I wasnt ready for this one.  I actually thought it might be skunked.  But by the time I finished it I wanted another one.  The sharp fruity flavor is actually very refreshing.
The stout that I compare all other stouts to.  Even though its fake its nice that theyve found a way to simulate a draft stout in a can or bottle.

beer_brewer_name: Old Dominion Brewing Company (Coastal Brewing Co.)
review_blob: A drinkable slightly strong American bock.

One of my favorite beers and so far my favorite spiced beers.  I had it on tap for the first time years ago in Virginia.  It is not yet distributed here in California so everytime I visit my in-laws in Delaware for Christmas I drive over an hour into PA to get some - its worth it!

We had this beer on tap the first night at Jasper Park Lodge in Canada.  Maybe it was the incredible views, wonderful smell, and tranquility of Jasper but this beer was great.  An amber colored ale with a slightly strong but pure and clean taste.
